        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Traveler Reimbursements Underscore Equity Act of 2020 or the</b> <b>TRUE Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill requires an air carrier receiving federal loans or grants under the Coronavirus Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act due to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) to certify to the Department of Transportation that it will reimburse a consumer amounts paid for a flight canceled by such air carrier or the consumer during the COVID-19 emergency period.</p> <p> The requirement does not apply in the case of a passenger who was reimbursed amounts paid by a third party or through travel protection insurance.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
